Mini DPU Controller

A simplified ASIC-style Mini DPU (Data Processing Unit) Controller project designed for learning:

RTL Design :
APB protocol
FSM-based controller design
DMA-style data movement
ASIC verification methodology
SoC subsystem integration

This project models a small hardware accelerator that autonomously copies data between memory regions inside SRAM under CPU/APB control.

Project Goals :

The main objective of this project is to learn and demonstrate:

APB slave interface design
Memory-mapped register architecture
FSM-controlled datapath operation
DMA-style memory transfers
Interrupt generation and handling
Directed verification methodology
End-to-end data integrity checking

High-Level Architecture
                +----------------------+
APB Master ---->|   APB Slave IF       |
                +----------------------+
                           |
                           v
                +----------------------+
                |   DPU Controller     |
                | FSM + Transfer Logic |
                +----------------------+
                           |
                           v
                +----------------------+
                |      SRAM Model      |
                +----------------------+

Functional Overview :

The Mini DPU Controller performs Memory-to-memory data copy operation inside a single SRAM.

The CPU/software:

Programs source address
Programs destination address
Programs transfer length
Starts DPU operation

The DPU then:

reads source data
writes destination data
repeats until transfer completes
generates interrupt

Key Features :

Control Path -
APB3 simplified slave interface
Memory-mapped registers
START control
STATUS monitoring
Interrupt support

Datapath -
Internal SRAM model
Source/Destination address pointers
Transfer counter
Buffered data movement

Controller -
FSM-based architecture
Autonomous transfer engine
Error detection
DONE/ERROR interrupt generation

